message.content: A Orthetrum cancellatum is a species of dragonfly belonging to the family of Libellulidae. It is commonly known as the Black-tailed Skimmer. The male has a blue-gray abdomen and a black tail tip, while the female has a yellow-brown abdomen with a black stripe along the top. They have transparent wings with brown or black veins. They grow to a wingspan of about 70 mm. They are found in habitats such as ponds, lakes, and slow-moving rivers across Europe and Asia. They are active from June to August.
